overview: The user initiated a request for a complete aesthetic overhaul of
  their sleep questionnaire app, aiming to transform its generic appearance into
  a more polished and calming experience. The agent began by thoroughly
  reviewing the existing visual design, identifying key areas for improvement
  such as the color palette, typography, spacing, form elements, and overall
  visual interest. A new sleep-themed color palette with deep indigos, purples,
  and teal accents was introduced. The main questionnaire form layout was
  redesigned with decorative background elements, an enhanced progress
  indicator, and a subtle star pattern on the card header. The welcome screen
  (IntroSection) was significantly improved with a hero section, feature cards,
  and refined alert styling. All UI components, including checkboxes, radio
  buttons, sliders, and the progress bar, received updated styling for a more
  modern and cohesive look. Crucially, all 14 form sections were systematically
  updated to replace old gray-boxed groupings with the new card-style,
  theme-consistent designs. The report section also received a visual refresh
  with consistent card headers and improved content styling. The agent ensured
  all changes were applied consistently and verified the absence of linting
  errors, resulting in a significantly more professional, calming, and visually
  appealing application experience.
